> "Yo, what is going on here, guys?"

**Wade Brown** — *defending the halberd as unassuming*
> "It's a little more subtle, though. It doesn't have a bunch of, like, fine filigree or anything, right?"

**Vukradin** — *providing the diplomatic cover story*
> "This is the halberd you've had all along, you just sharpened it on the sharpen."
> "You're mistaken."
> "This is the halberd you've had all along, you just sharpened it on a sharpening stone, and it just looks more lethal."
> "That's totally fine. You can just get your halberd as much as you want. No problem with that."

**GM** — *adding a physical detail that complicates the cover story*
> "And it looks a little waterlogged."

