**[Valphine's Theology — Lathander as Power, Not Mercy]**
- Kostadis articulates his conception of Valphine's faith; Valphine confirms it; Vukradin draws the meta-conclusion.

**GM** — *expounding on Valphine's unorthodox reading of Lathander*
> "This is not you, Wade, this is."
> "This is lucrative."
> "I just wanna say that the… the… person who should be making these comments is… is Valphine. So, Valphine, you are… you are the… you are the, chosen of Lathander."
> "Lathander approves."

**GM** — *delivering the full theological argument*
> "I see Valphine, but Valphine, she is your character, so…"
> "It's 24x7 power, you know?"
> "Not, you know, the kind of power that's just tender, it's, like, hurting people 12 hours a day."
> "And when it's not hurting them, they beg for it to come back."
> "And they're afraid of it not being around. I mean, like, this all fits Malfinay's personality perfectly."
> "And now she feels… she feels closer to Lathander, who approves of her… Curious new interpretation of his power."

**Valphine** — *confirming the reading*
> "Perfect."

**Vukradin** — *articulating the meta-observation*
> "I like that… I like that the cleric is changing the god instead of the god changing the cleric."
> "What's a new one?"

**GM** — *reframing it as D&D orthodoxy*
> "That's how it always has been in Dungeons & Dragons."
> "The god… the gods are… the gods reflect the choices, not the other way around."
